<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | CourtScope"><section class="hero"><div class="prose-width"><p class="eyebrow">Public policy</p><h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p class="lede">CourtScope minimizes personal information and separates public data from restricted evidence.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="prose-width"><div class="card"><p>Public case pages never display defendant names. Correction reporter emails are private and scheduled for deletion 90 days after closure. Raw IP addresses are not retained; salted abuse-prevention hashes may be used. Restricted source artifacts remain private unless a lawful, ethical public release is approved.</p><h2>What controls</h2><p>Official source terms, applicable law, dataset-specific notices, and the current published CourtScope methodology control where they are more specific. Contact <a href="mailto:info@courtscope.org">info@courtscope.org</a> for questions.</p><p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 11, 2026</p></div></div></section></BaseLayout>